"{\"uid\": \"thenews.com.pk-print-1218969-canada-s-b-boy-phil-wizard-wins-first-olympic-breaking-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS: Canada\\u00b4s B-Boy Phil Wizard won the inaugural Olympic men\\u00b4s breaking gold in Paris on Saturday, and said he hoped it \\\"opens doors to people\\\" involved in the high-energy dance sport.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 187, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 83, \"end\": 88, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999413376, \"rank\": 5.857369834970401e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phil Wizard, whose real name is Philip Kim, beat France\\u00b4s B-Boy Dany Dann in the final amid the opulent grandeur of the Place de la Concorde, with B-Boy Victor of the US taking bronze.\", \"from\": 189, \"to\": 373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 221, \"end\": 231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\", \"score\": 0.9999999991202912, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philip Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\"}, {\"begin\": 309, \"end\": 329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 0.9999999550350377, \"rank\": 4.496491214688404e-08, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}, {\"begin\": 336, \"end\": 341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4252544406629943e-36, \"text\": \"B-Boy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\"}, {\"begin\": 342, \"end\": 348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.9997587318972343, \"rank\": 0.00023637129891402356, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 356, \"end\": 358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"score\": 0.9452885292320061, \"rank\": 0.04260829457212623, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking, better known as breakdancing, is making its first and possibly last appearance at the Olympics, having been left off the programme for Los Angeles 2028.\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 520, \"end\": 536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles 2028\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phil Wizard said breaking was \\\"an underappreciated sport\\\" and hoped its Olympic debut would change people\\u00b4s minds.\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope that today was a perfect example of showing the world how incredible breaking is -- that was truly my only goal here,\\\" said the 27-year-old, a former world champion.\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I\\u00b4m so grateful and so happy to come out with the win, but more than anything I just wanted to show the world what breaking is.\\\"\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 959, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition saw 16 dancers, known as B-Boys, going head-to-head in a series of battles, starting with a pool stage before moving to a knock-out round.\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 1115, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Phil Wizard had the crowd against him in the final against local hero Dany Dann, a 36-year-old with blue hair whose real name is Danis Civil.\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Canadian soon had them eating out of his hand thanks to his incredible routine, for which the judges awarded him a 3-0 victory.\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1267, \"end\": 1275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9215388791829883, \"rank\": 0.046083683276507734, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was stressed out of my mind,\\\" said Phil Wizard.\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It\\u00b4s been a whirlwind of emotion.\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1482, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I cried my eyes out because I was so scared to do this.\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1538, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There\\u00b4s been a lot of pressure, a lot of expectations -- I\\u00b4m glad I was able to deliver.\\\"\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Danny Dann, a former European champion, said he felt like he had \\\"represented breaking\\\" to the world.\", \"from\": 1632, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1653, \"end\": 1670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Figure_Skating_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9984076745910907, \"rank\": 0.0007787051941659369, \"text\": \"European champion\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Figure_Skating_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Figure_Skating_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I\\u00b4m delighted, I really didn\\u00b4t think I would win this medal,\\\" he said, revealing that he dyed his hair blue because it was his \\\"lucky colour\\\".\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just went there to see how things would go and I\\u00b4m going home with a silver medal.\\\"\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1965, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the spectacular moves on show, Phil Wizard said the panel of judges were looking for \\\"something new every round\\\".\", \"from\": 1967, \"to\": 2088, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You may well think it\\u00b4s the most explosive, crazy dynamic movements that score the most points,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2196, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But in breaking there\\u00b4s a lot of different categories and the most important thing is originality and diversity of movement.\\\"\", \"from\": 2197, \"to\": 2323, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The B-Boys perform on a circular stage, accompanied by DJs pumping out hip-hop classics and MCs hyping up the crowd.\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2441, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking originated in the block parties held in the Bronx in New York in the 1970s.\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2496, \"end\": 2501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"score\": 0.9999999938368092, \"rank\": 6.163211623318487e-09, \"text\": \"Bronx\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\"}, {\"begin\": 2505, \"end\": 2513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999998943928914, \"rank\": 1.0489474933284812e-07, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"B-Boy Victor, also known as Victor Montalvo, said the competition represented \\\"the true essence of hip hop and breaking culture\\\".\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2529, \"end\": 2534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4252544406629943e-36, \"text\": \"B-Boy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\"}, {\"begin\": 2535, \"end\": 2541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.9997587318972343, \"rank\": 0.00023637129891402356, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 2557, \"end\": 2563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.9997587318972343, \"rank\": 0.00023637129891402356, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 2564, \"end\": 2572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalvo_Beach\", \"score\": 0.9894755037246608, \"rank\": 0.0064197935718665715, \"text\": \"Montalvo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalvo_Beach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montalvo_Beach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We just want to make sure that we show everyone that it\\u00b4s a dance, first of all,\\\" said Victor, who beat Japan\\u00b4s Shigekix for the bronze medal.\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2747, \"end\": 2753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.9997587318972343, \"rank\": 0.00023637129891402356, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It\\u00b4s all about self-expression, it\\u00b4s all about originality.\", \"from\": 2804, \"to\": 2864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00b4s not just about big moves.\\\"\", \"from\": 2865, \"to\": 2896, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Japan\\u00b4s B-Girl Ami won the women\\u00b4s gold on Friday, beating Lithuania\\u00b4s B-Girl Nicka in the final.\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 2995, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2025.\", \"from\": 2997, \"to\": 3014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The News International, All Rights Reserved\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3015, \"end\": 3037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_News_International\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The News International\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_News_International\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_News_International\"}]}]}"